1.12
log
@DEBUGLIBS has been broken since the gcc4 switch, so delete it.  CFLAGS
contains -g by default anyway

problem noted by Edgar Pettijohn (edgar (at) pettijohn-web.com)
ok millert@@ kettenis@@ deraadt@@
@
text
@# $OpenBSD: Makefile,v 1.11 2016/03/30 06:38:42 jmc Exp $

LIB=	panel
SRCS=	p_above.c p_below.c p_bottom.c p_delete.c p_hidden.c p_hide.c p_move.c \
	p_new.c p_replace.c p_show.c p_top.c p_update.c p_user.c p_win.c panel.c
HDRS=	panel.h
MAN=	panel.3
CFLAGS+= -I${.CURDIR}/../libcurses

includes:
	@@cd ${.CURDIR}; for i in ${HDRS}; do \
	  cmp -s $$i ${DESTDIR}/usr/include/$$i || \
	  ${INSTALL} ${INSTALL_COPY} -m 444 -o $(BINOWN) -g $(BINGRP) $$i \
	  ${DESTDIR}/usr/include; done

.include <bsd.own.mk>

afterinstall:
	-cd ${DESTDIR}${LIBDIR}; \
	for i in ${_LIBS}; do \
	    ln -f $$i `echo $$i | sed 's/panel/panelw/'`; \
	done

.include <bsd.lib.mk>
@


1.11
log
@for some time now mandoc has not required MLINKS to function
correctly - logically complete that now by removing MLINKS from base;

authors need only to ensure there is an entry in NAME for any function/
util being added. MLINKS will still work, and remain for perl to ease
upgrades;

ok nicm (curses) bcook (ssl)
ok schwarze, who provided a lot of feedback and assistance
ok tb natano jung
@
